projects. | Mei Decor, Noida | | 2024-Present |  Planning and scheduling construction activities, ensuring adherence to project timelines.  Supervising site execution, vendor coordination, and material management.  Resolving on-site technical issues and ensuring safety and quality standards.  Preparing progress reports, RFIs, and technical documentation for management. Senior Engineer - civil ||  Monitored construction progress and ensured execution as per drawings. | Express Builders, Noida | | 2021-2024 |  Coordinated with design and procurement teams to streamline site workflow.  Maintained safety compliance and managed vendor and subcontractor activities. Site Engineer ||  Managed quantity surveying, site coordination, and execution using Mivan systems. | Eins Technik Formwork System, Noida | | 2019-2021 |  Liaised with clients and consultants to ensure timely delivery. Site Engineer ||  Managed construction planning and execution for high-rise towers (North Eye, ORB Tower). | B.E. Billimoria & Co. Ltd., New Delhi | | 2015-2019 |  Supervising site execution, vendor coordination, and material management.  Resolving on-site technical issues and ensuring safety and quality standards.  Preparing progress reports, RFIs, and technical documentation for management.  Handled civil execution and supervision for HPCL petrol pump projects. OVERALL JOB RESPONSIBILITIES: ➢ Checking and assuring that the construction is as per the final issued for construction drawings and project specifications and construction schedules. ➢ Have worked or have been working on many projects for government and private sector clients. ➢ Detailed level knowledge of Site Inspection, Site Supervision, Quantities Take-off, BOQ, Project Estimations and Tender Documents Preparation. ➢ Surveying & Leveling work including using Theodolites, Dumpy Levels & Total Station. ➢ Preparation of tender quantities. ➢ Preparation of monthly work schedule. ➢ Working knowledge about AutoCAD, MS-Office, MS-Excel. ➢ Preparing separate quantity take-off for material procurement with respect to the method statements and approved manufacturer’s specifications. ➢ Preparing the standard quantities and bar bending schedules. ➢ Responsible for monthly running account bills preparation & Subcontractor bills checking. ➢ Preparing the rate analysis for variation orders. ➢ Preparation and submission of variations and agreeing with clients and consultants. ➢ Making monthly presentations on monthly billing, monthly budget. ➢ Engineering coordination with Design team for releasing construction Drawings as per the schedule. ➢ Material procurement, indenting of Construction material as well as bought out items based on the Drawings & contract. ➢ Cement, steel and finishing items reconciliation & preparing standard quantities and bar bending schedules. ➢ Preparation of job close out reports and analyzing with theoretical quantities vs actual quantities and preparation of AS- Built drawings. ➢ Developing strong relationship with Client, subcontractor and team members. ➢ Summarizing the site progress daily basis based on the execution team reports and monitoring with respect to the schedule. ➢ Continuous monitoring the team to follow proper permit system and HSE requirements for execution of the job. ➢ Execution and supervision of critical and priority civil works.  Hands-on experience in Mivan shuttering for large-scale residential towers.  Successfully handled 66-storey high-rise building project scheduling and execution.  Currently leading turnkey interior and renovation works for premium clients.  Skilled in identifying project risks and implementing corrective measures.  Expertise in site resource management, technical drawing reviews, and formwork systems."}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Mr. Shubham Poddar.pdf', 'Name: Shubham Poddar

